problem_text: Figure 23-35 shows a closed Gaussian surface in the shape of a cube of edge length $2.00 \mathrm{~m}$, with one corner at $x_1=5.00 \mathrm{~m}, y_1=4.00$ $\mathrm{m}$. The cube lies in a region where the electric field vector is given by $\vec{E}=-3.00 \hat{i}-4.00 y^2 \hat{j}+3.00 \hat{\mathrm{k}} \mathrm{N} / \mathrm{C}$, with $y$ in meters. What is the net charge contained by the cube?
